                            <comment id="13926347" author="srikanth235" created="Mon, 10 Mar 2014 22:27:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adding the patch which adds the entry for property hbase.regionserver.region.split.policy with the corresponding value as org.apache.hadoop.hbase.regionserver.IncreasingToUpperBoundRegionSplitPolicy.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13926352" author="bbeaudreault" created="Mon, 10 Mar 2014 22:29:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I know this is probably outside the scope of this particular issue, but I think the ConstantSizeSplitPolicy is a more reasonable default than what is currently configured.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13926356" author="bbeaudreault" created="Mon, 10 Mar 2014 22:30:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;org.apache.hadoop.hbase.regionserver.ConstantSizeRegionSplitPolicy that is&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13926364" author="srikanth235" created="Mon, 10 Mar 2014 22:37:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://hbase.apache.org/0.94/apidocs/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/regionserver/RegionSplitPolicy.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hbase.apache.org/0.94/apidocs/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/regionserver/RegionSplitPolicy.html&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;br/&gt;
it is mentioned that default policy since 0.94.0 is IncreasingToUpperBoundRegionSplitPolicy, hence I used the value of org.apache.hadoop.hbase.regionserver.IncreasingToUpperBoundRegionSplitPolicy  as opposed to org.apache.hadoop.hbase.regionserver.ConstantSizeRegionSplitPolicy.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13926366" author="jmhsieh" created="Mon, 10 Mar 2014 22:38:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=srikanth235&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;srikanth235&quot;&gt;Srikanth Srungarapu&lt;/a&gt; Can you add other options like ConstantSizeSplitPolicy to the description section.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13926406" author="srikanth235" created="Mon, 10 Mar 2014 23:06:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated the description with other available policies and attaching the updated patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13926454" author="jmhsieh" created="Mon, 10 Mar 2014 23:42:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks great! This doesn&apos;t change any defaults so committing to 0.94/0.96/0.98/trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
